This paper deals with graph databases and query languages, which are typically studied in the database (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also proposes an algorithm for efficient graph joining, which involves indexing and searching large amounts of data, making it relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents experimental results comparing the proposed algorithm to existing graph query languages, which involves performance evaluation and optimization, making it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
